==Description==

The [[Image:Sketcher_ConstrainGroup.svg|24px]] [[Sketcher_ConstrainGroup|Sketcher ConstrainGroup]] tool constrains the selected geometries together as a single entity. The position and size of the grouped geometries can be defined by constraining the automatically generated construction line. 

==Usage==

# Select geometries in the sketch.
# There are several ways to invoke the tool:
#* Press the {{Button|[[Image:Sketcher_ConstrainGroup.svg|16px]] [[Sketcher_ConstrainGroup|Group Constrain]]}} button.
#* Select the {{MenuCommand|Sketch → Constraints → [[Image:Sketcher_ConstrainGroup.svg|16px]] Group Constrain}} option from the menu.
#* Use the keyboard shortcut: {{KEY|K}} then {{KEY|G}}.
# The selected geometries will be grouped.

==Notes==
* Constraints applied to grouped edges are ignored as long as the Group constraint is present.


